:INFO
The Novel I Finished and Could Not Recommend to Everyone
The Troop is the most physically disturbing novel I have finished. Nick Cutter \
puts a group of Boy Scouts on an island in the Canadian wilderness and introduces \
a stranger who is infected with a parasite engineered to consume its host. The \
horror is biological and specific and it does not look away. I finished it in \
two days and told exactly zero people to read it because the content is not for \
every reader. I am telling you so you can make that decision yourself.

:NOTE
There is no redemptive arc here. This book is content to unsettle you and leave.

:QUOTE [subtitle:Nick Cutter, quotetype:PLAIN]
There are things in the dark places that have waited longer than memory permits.

:JOURNEY
Reading The Troop
Section
Tension
- Island setup | 4 | Efficient tension | Dread arrives before the stranger does
- Stranger's chapters | 5 | Biological horror | Specific and genuinely disturbing
- Boys' survival | 4 | Restrained chaos | The Lord of the Flies dimension held in check
- The ending | 4 | Bleak and honest | Does exactly what this kind of horror should do

:NOW
Recommending this to exactly one person I know and not to anyone else \
because the content requires a specific kind of reader to find it worthwhile.

:NOTE
This book has graphic content involving harm to children and animals. \
That is not a spoiler. That is something to know before you decide to read it.
